				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=104222&amp;sid=a7b65202ba97767929df8bcf4bec52df"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The design decision by SoE to destroy augments when they are dissolved off items seems to me to serve no useful game-balance purpose. Even from a time-sink point of view it is as likely to cause people not to bother with LDoN augments as it is to make them play it for longer.
<br />

<br />
It does not seem to have anything in its favour, and so I suspect that if enough people /feedback to SoE we could get it changed.
<br />

<br />
It would be easy enough to change the program so that when you apply the solvent you get back both your item and the augment, so that you can then attach it to another item.
<br />

<br />
I cannot imagine that a single one of the player base would have any genuine disagreement such a change.
<br />

<br />
So let's all feedback it until SoE get fed up and change it.<br />_________________<br />Elder Hzark Kuezk (& Sslth)
<br />
Iksar Feral Lord
<br />
Grandmaster (250) Tailor
<br />
Torv
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=688699" target="_blank">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=688699</a>
<br />

