				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OK, having thought about this, my original suggestion is not really balanced because it would allow people to swap procs on their weapons for certain mobs by nipping over to the WF camp before the raid.
<br />

<br />
So here is a nerfed suggestion which would not cause any balance problems but would still allow players to keep augments they had spent lots of AP on when they upgrade the slot:
<br />

<br />
Allow a 4th type of solvent that dissolves (destroys) the item and leaves the augment(s) intact. Not too painful for obsolete No Drop items, but fairly painful for saleable items.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Elder Hzark Kuezk (& Sslth)
