			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">This would be nice, but I doubt SOE would implement. </span>
<br />

<br />
Allow players to craft/tradeskill a unique solvent.
<br />

<br />
This special solvent would be No Drop, perhaps require the tradeskills of 220 to on the final combine. The items used to create the solvent would be rare drops only in the adventure themes.
<br />

<br />
The no drop vial created to contain the unique solvent could require a higherlevel tradeskill, perhaps 250.
<br />

<br />
The items used to create the solvent would be rare but tradable, however the final solvent itself would be No Drop.
<br />

<br />
The special solvent would remove any augment from any item.
<br />

<br />
The removed augment would be re-useable and perhaps also returnable to the Ldon merchants, but not tradable to other players.
<br />

<br />
A removed augment would NOT loose its original effect, stats, requirements or focus.
<br />

<br />
However if a player wishes to return an augment, the augment returned would only be worth half the point cost it was originally. 
<br />

<br />
Because the augment was used, the player would be credited half the cost of the items original value.
<br />

<br />
The time, effort & many hours invested to earn the necessary points would then not go to waste, and the augment a person worked so very hard to achieve would be re-useable for a different desired item.
<br />

<br />
For the time, effort, teamwork & thought required to successfully complete a Time level Ldon raid ~ those augments should also be allowed the same.
<br />

<br />
Used raid augments if returned would be credited half their value, however the returned augment would be absorbed by the NPC and not be purchasable.
<br />

<br />
I personally would like to continue to use my "Cherished Companion Shard" in the future ~ until I find a pet focus item greater then this.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=697663">Elder Kilantiz Kylong</a>
<br />
&lt;Fires of Heaven&gt;
<br />
Beast ~ Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
