Yep. Basic idea behind augments is that you can't have your pudding and eat it. You have to be careful, plan ahead - or just spend the points and know you'll outgrown them. Which is OK - augments are free. Adv points happen on top of xp and plat, for fast and generally easy missions. 
<br />

<br />
"Have your pudding and eat it"... sigh, the more I hear peoples wanting to make things easier and denouncing anything vaguely looking like a constraint as "un-fun", the more I feel and sound like an old moralistic codger.
