			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First of all to Klantiz: the bulk of your idea has merit but nix the no drop on the final part. It's getting really annoying that the fix for everything is tradeskill oriented. Dyes for LDoN, the cured ethereal energies for ornate / elemental, etc. Doing tradeskills is its own reward (not to mention Signet of the Arcane, 8th shawl, 10th ring, etc). It shouldn't be a prerequisite for something completley unrelated such as augments.
<br />

<br />
That said, there's really no point to allowing augments to be not destroyed. There's simply no longevity to LDoN that way. As it is now, everyone and their brother will be going for 5 Solid/Radiant Coals of Prowess if they want to keep their existing gear, or perhaps the FT2 chest aug, etc. Everyone can select some augment for each of their slots now. If augments weren't destroyed, once you've bought all these augments, you are <span style="font-weight: bold">done</span> with LDoN.
<br />

<br />
With the sole exceptions of buying type 8 equivalents of your type 7's when moving into time, or buying type 7/8's to put in your elemental/time gear replacing any LDoN gear you bought, there would never be a reason to continue with LDoN. And no, 10 missons for 2hp is in fact not worth it.
<br />

<br />
So as others have said, plan your purchases carefully. You shouldn't be able to do 23 ruj adventures, get your SCoP and put it in your Black Pantherskin Tunic, then replace it and put it in your PSC, then in your Ornate, then in your IVotFT. Call it a time sink, but I have to agree with sony on this one. Either wait for your IVotFT (I will be.. no way in hell I'm auging my ornate) or aug your ornate and spend another 1150 later.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
