			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As for buying lesser priced goods, it happens all the time as is.  If you need an upgrade in a particular slot NOW, then why wait to get the best of the best especially if you dont plan to spend all your time in LDoN?  Case and point I have several guildies that bought a belt that was the "second" best they could buy.  Sure they could have waited, spent more points, etc etc.  But they were looking for a moderate upgrade in a slot they were lacking.
<br />
Why is this?  Because they dont want to be committed to doing LDoN every hour of every day till they have that item.  They did it because it was about 2x faster doing it that way.  They need that time saved to go hit other places, raid, flag, etc etc.
<br />
I think the design of this system is great.  They put a big enough "time sink" into it so that you dont walk in walk out and have an extremely super piece of armor.  It encourages you to save and buy some items in LDoN, at the same time as looking for upgrades in other areas.  (Elemental planes etc)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
